text: Run by a old couple. Tried the pork chop with fried rice. Good portiom for the price.
Very friendly elderly couple maning the store. Wide variety of old school western dishes. Always happy to serve customers.
Typical kind of western food old school. Taste nice for the chicken chop n sauce. For fries probably try to use the fresh fried ones. Thks.
Previously from 327 , I would say their standard is good.
My to go place for old school western food. Price is also reasonable
